    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="411" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 6, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Lord Lyons</hi>: I think it not
                            unreasonable, in view of the late transactions at Mobile, to ask that
                            renewed instructions may be given to British war vessels on the coast of
                            the United States to avoid all other than legitimate occupations in
                            their visits to the ports held by the insurgents. I am, with great
                            respect, your humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right. Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
